      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHEIKH OF TWEAK (1) goes very well at the course with two wins and a placing from six starts. Below best last time at Ballarat (22.65) in a Grade 5, finishing a 6 length fourth. Looks well placed and should feature. CITY LIMIT (8) was in the money again last time and not beaten far when second (24.29) at Bendigo in a Grade 5. Well placed here and can atone this time. PAW VERITY (3) stalked the lead and fought on well to finish 3 lengths away in third (22.41) at this track in a Grade 5 over 390m. Form from her last run is proving to be solid. Overdue and gets her chance. DOONGALLA ADAM (2) is always hard to beat when he races here at this trip.",
